'''Öshül-küllösh''' was a waterfall on [[Ellor Eshúrizel]] according to [[Michael George Ramer]] in ''[[The Notion Club Papers]]''.<ref name=History>{{SD|2c}}, pp. 198-9, 218</ref>

[[Nicholas Guildford]] reported in the [[Notion Club Papers]] that [[Alwin Arundel Lowdham]] had claimed that after the meeting, Ramer had revealed to him that he had thought that Öshül-küllösh meant "''Falling Water''".<ref name=History/>
